Class NewSighting

java.lang.Object
  Activity
      org.hfoss.posit.NewSighting

public class NewSighting
extends Activity

NewSighting is an activity for recording instances of the record that we are recording. Originally designed for tracking Hawks, it includes the following features: - GPS co-ordinates are added to the database[Sightings/Instance table] using the location service - The type of finding is detected and saved. - Weather for the city is detected and saved along with the data. What is a sighting? A sighting, in general is referred to all the instances of the finds that the device gathers. So, sighting is a more particular term to represent the more general term "find." A sighting is bound to a find by the recordId of the "find" which is unique to the finds. Not being used in this version
